<h2>Overview</h2>



The Comserv Mail System provides functionality for sending emails and managing mail configurations across different sites. This document explains how to use and configure the mail system, including troubleshooting common issues.



<h2>Components</h2>



The mail system consists of the following components:



<ol><li>**Mail Controller** (<code>Comserv::Controller::Mail</code>): Handles mail-related routes and actions</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Mail Model** (<code>Comserv::Model::Mail</code>): Provides email sending functionality</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Configuration Storage**: Stores SMTP settings in the database</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Templates**: Email templates and configuration forms</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Fallback Mechanism**: Alternative email sending method when primary method fails</li></ol>



<h2>Mail Controller</h2>



The Mail Controller (<code>/lib/Comserv/Controller/Mail.pm</code>) provides the following actions:



<ul><li><code>index</code>: Displays the mail page with webmail links</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>send_welcome_email</code>: Sends a welcome email to new users</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>add_mail_config_form</code>: Displays the form to add mail configuration</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>add_mail_config</code>: Processes the mail configuration form submission</li></ul>



<h3>Routes</h3>



<ul><li><code>/mail</code> - Main mail page with webmail links</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>/mail/add_mail_config_form</code> - Form to add mail configuration</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>/mail/add_mail_config</code> - Endpoint to process mail configuration</li></ul>



<h2>Mail Model</h2>



The Mail Model (<code>/lib/Comserv/Model/Mail.pm</code>) provides the following methods:



<ul><li><code>send_email</code>: Sends an email using the configured SMTP settings</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>_get_smtp_config</code>: Retrieves SMTP configuration from the database</li></ul>



<h3>Email Sending Process</h3>



<ol><li>Retrieve SMTP configuration from the database</li></ol>

<ol><li>Create an email using Email::Simple</li></ol>

<ol><li>Set up SMTP transport with the configuration</li></ol>

<ol><li>Send the email using Email::Sender::Simple</li></ol>

<ol><li>Log the result (success or failure)</li></ol>



<h2>Configuration</h2>



<h3>SMTP Configuration</h3>



SMTP settings are stored in the <code>site_config</code> table with the following keys:



<ul><li><code>smtp_host</code>: SMTP server hostname</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>smtp_port</code>: SMTP server port</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>smtp_username</code>: SMTP authentication username</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>smtp_password</code>: SMTP authentication password</li></ul>

<ul><li><code>smtp_from</code>: Default sender email address</li></ul>



<h3>Adding Mail Configuration</h3>



To add mail configuration for a site:



<ol><li>Navigate to <code>/mail/add_mail_config_form</code></li></ol>

<ol><li>Enter the site ID and SMTP settings</li></ol>

<ol><li>Submit the form</li></ol>

<ol><li>The configuration will be stored in the database</li></ol>



